# Triangle-only sample for Combobulate. An octahedron (8 triangular faces).
#
# Each face is wound so (V1-V0) x (V2-V0) points outward. No vt entries —
# the renderer uses the per-face fallback colour palette.
#
# This file exercises:
#   * Triangle parsing (model.Triangles).
#   * ObjGeometry quad-recovery preprocess: pairs of coplanar adjacent
#     triangles cannot be fused here because the octahedron has no two
#     triangles in the same plane, so every triangle stays as a triangle
#     CachedQuad. This is the worst case for the triangle path — eight
#     SpriteVisuals with eight CompositionGeometricClips.
#   * Back-face culling and painter sort across triangular faces.

# 6 octahedron vertices: tips on each axis.
v  1  0  0    # 1  +X
v -1  0  0    # 2  -X
v  0  1  0    # 3  +Y
v  0 -1  0    # 4  -Y
v  0  0  1    # 5  +Z
v  0  0 -1    # 6  -Z

# Upper hemisphere (4 triangles meeting at +Y)
f 5 1 3       # +Z, +X, +Y   normal (+X+Z+Y)/sqrt(3) — outward
f 1 6 3       # +X, -Z, +Y   outward
f 6 2 3       # -Z, -X, +Y
f 2 5 3       # -X, +Z, +Y

# Lower hemisphere (4 triangles meeting at -Y)
f 1 5 4       # +X, +Z, -Y
f 6 1 4       # -Z, +X, -Y
f 2 6 4       # -X, -Z, -Y
f 5 2 4       # +Z, -X, -Y
